{
  "stem": "10572.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some of them jumped into the open latrines.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Dante's It was hell like it had never been described.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And nobody could describe it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And many other things that I've read later on about it-- it is impossible to describe all of those things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maybe by trying to do crazy things and being myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw, after I was there for about a week, I saw a kapo.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A 'kapo' comes from the Italian, 'head.' And they use this from the Italian fascists, this term, because Mussolini also had concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the kapos were professional criminals, professional criminals who, when they had served their term, the Gestapo would pick them as anti-social.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Gestapo could arrest anybody without any legal documents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were put into concentration camps and were put in charge of us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And by feeding them an extra piece of bread or even, maybe, a piece of sausage that we didn't know, they would be doing things that normal human beings wouldn't do.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one day, one day, a 70-year-old man-- I still see him-- picked up a cigarette butt.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And smoking was, of course, completely taboo.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he probably was an addict to nicotine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And an SS officer had dropped the cigarette butt, and he picked it up and tried to smoke it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the kapo came and used his club-- they were the only ones who had arms in the camp, not the SS officer-- didn't carry any arms in the compound.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he took his club and hit this man over the head.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I heard the head split.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and I went to this man, obviously having lost my my rationale-- you know, that you don't talk ethics to a kapo in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I said to him, I said, if there's a God in heaven, some day you will pay for this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had a number.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "By that time, I had a uniform on, a striped uniform with my number.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the wash kitchen was a place in Buchenwald where the people who had lost their mind would be taken to.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they gave them hot and cold showers to bring them back to sanity.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In reality, they got pneumonia and died there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had two friends, one of them a very close friend of mine, who later on stayed a very close friend of mine when he was-- became a great rabbi in Olympia Fields, Frank Rosenthal.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was-- had volunteered for the wash kitchen, to-- together with another rabbi, Egon [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Loewenstein, ?] to be able to say Kaddish for those who died.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had gone-- before, before I went to the wash kitchen, I went to Baracke 1A, the barrack I stayed in, to tell my brother-in-law and-- what had happened to me so that they knew where I was-- where they finished me off.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I went there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I repeated and told them what I'd said, they put me over a block and gave me the usual punishment of 25 slashes with a two-by-four over my back and broke vertebra, broke discs that I have lived with the rest of my life.",
      "word_count": 46
    }
  ],
